The paper proposes a visual recognition system for bin-picking using a 3D vision sensor attached to a manipulator. This involves detecting the poses of randomly stacked objects using a part of the visual image taken at the current picking trial where it is different from the previous trial. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category, as it deals with manipulation tasks using a robot arm. Additionally, the paper involves computer vision techniques for object detection, which could place it in the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The iterative nature of the proposed system suggests that it could involve machine learning techniques, which could place it in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the use of a 3D vision sensor and manipulator suggests that the paper could also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
